text: Net2Phone is allowed by the University firewall
H323 video conferencing is allowed by the University firewall
POP3 and secure POP are allowed by the University firewall
Students have a quota of 5 GB per day The quota is reset at 6am
You may not run FTP, telnet, peer-to-peer, HTTP, IRC, DNS and mail servers on ResNet or UIC wireless-connected devices
These network security changes include blocking traffic from the Internet into the UW network over FTP
The UC Davis network is continually scanned for prohibited activities and network threats.
Telnet is allowed by the University firewall
Currently, the University of Illinois does not have any rate limits set in place
CIS restricts traffic that is known to cause damage to the network or hosts on it, such as NETBIOS
Elements of network security currently include the following four solutions: Network Border Infrastructure System, Intrusion Prevention System, Firewalls and Custom Unit Firewalls
You may not run any services (e.g., FTP services,listservers,P2P file sharing servers, publishing files via generic file services, etc.) via ResNet or NYURoam wireless networks
